-- Penguins Sign Crosby to $100 Million Extension, TSN Says
-- B y   L a r r y   S i d d o n s
-- 2012-06-28T16:56:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-28/penguins-sign-sidney-crosby-to-100-million-extension-tsn-says.html
Sidney Crosby  is signing a $100
million contract extension with the Pittsburgh Penguins,  TSN.com
reported .  The Canadian-based website didn’t say where it got the
information. It said the deal would average about $9 million a
year and is expected to be announced on July 1.  Crosby, 24, had one year left on a five-year, $43.5 million
contract signed in 2007, TSN said.  He has battled concussions and neck injuries, playing 22
games last season with eight goals and 29 assists, according to
the  National Hockey League ’s website.  Pat Brisson, Crosby’s agent, and Frank Buonomo, a Penguins’
spokesman, didn’t immediately respond to e-mails seeking comment
on the report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at   msillup@bloomberg.net . 